Chinese President Xi Jinping congratulated Lukashenko on his re-election (10).

In a surprising turn, a 15-year-old boy named Brady Olson, also known as Deez Nuts, gained attention for running for president (9). Overview.Summary: In 2015, Belarus held its presidential election, with incumbent president Alexander Lukashenko winning by a landslide (1,4,20). The election campaign included debates and free air time for candidates on television and radio (2,3,5,6). The Central Electoral Commission registered four candidates aside from Lukashenko (8,10,12). The election also garnered international attention, with the Nobel Prize in Literature being awarded to Belarusian author Svetlana Alexievich (7). Lukashenko's visit to Vietnam in December of that year was also covered in the news (11). However, there were reports of opposition supporters calling for a boycott of the election (12). The election was monitored and covered by the Belarusian Association of Journalists (18). After the election, Lukashenko pardoned all six political prisoners (8).
